We then consider the case where the noise channel is close to the identity, meaning that the no-error outcome occurs with probability 1‚àíŒ∑. In the regime of small Œ∑ we extend our algorithm to achieve multiplicative precision 1¬±œµ (i.e., additive precision œµŒ∑) using just $O(1/œµ<sup>2</sup> Œ∑) \log(n/œµ)$ applications of the channel.},
