Applying our construction to certain concatenated stabilizer codes yields families of subsystem codes with constant-weight generators and with minimum distance d=n<sup>1‚àíœµ</sup>, where œµ=O(1/‚àölog n). For spatially local codes in D dimensions we nearly saturate a bound due to Bravyi and Terhal and achieve d=n<sup>1‚àíœµ‚àí1/D</sup>. Previously the best code distance achievable with constant-weight generators in any dimension, due to Freedman, Meyer and Luo, was O(‚àö(n log n)) for a stabilizer code.},
